Party System
=============
The party system is a means through which players can group together and
tackle NPCs as a team, sharing experience and gold between all members of
the party. It is assumed that all wizards already know what the party
system is and what it does.

This document briefly describes the means by which a wizard can create
code that will react to party events. The procedure is pretty simple.

1. An object is registered with the player using add_party_listener.
   [Ex. this_player()->add_party_listener(this_object())]
   
2. Any time a party event occurs, a specific function is called on the
   registered object. These functions are described below.
   
void party_add_member(mixed xNewMemberName)   : Called when a new member
                                                joins the player's party.
                                             
void party_remove_member(mixed xOldMemberName): Called when a member is
                                                removed from the player's
                                                party (leave/booted).
                                                 
void party_flag_adjust(mixed xFlag)           : Called when the "in party"
                                                flag is adjusted on the
                                                player, such as when a
                                                player joins/leaves a
                                                party. 1 = in party, 
                                                0 = not in party.
                                     
In addition to these particular callbacks, the following party related
functions exist on all players:

string *query_party_members()  -- Returns array of party member names
int query_in_party()           -- Returns 1 if in party, 0 otherwise
void end_party()               -- Remove the player from his party

varargs query_party_members_present(object oMember) --
                                  If you don't supply oMember, it will
                                  check all party members and return
                                  an object array of party members
                                  present (not including the player
                                  you're checking from). If none are
                                  present it returns 0.
                                  If you supply oMember, it will return
                                  1 if oMember is present, or 0 if not.
